"<div style="display: flex; gap: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(224, 224, 224); margin-bottom: 16px;"><button style="padding: 8px 16px; border-width: medium medium 2px; border-style: none none solid; border-color: currentcolor currentcolor rgb(33, 150, 243); border-image: initial; background-color: transparent; cursor: pointer; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-bottom: -1px; transition: 0.2s;">Preview</button><button style="padding: 8px 16px; border-width: medium; border-style: none; border-color: currentcolor; border-image: initial; background-color: transparent; cursor: pointer; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); margin-bottom: -1px; transition: 0.2s;">Write</button></div><div class="_Container_jix5i_1"><span contenteditable="false"></span><article style="display: block; padding: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: 1px solid rgb(221, 221, 221); border-radius: 8px; margin: 10px 0px;"><span>
</span><header style="display: block; padding: 10px; background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240); border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(221, 221, 221); margin-bottom: 10px;"><span>
</span><h1 style="display: block; font-size: 2em; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.67em 0px;"><span>Understanding </span><strong style="font-weight: bold;"><span>Nested HTML</span></strong><span> Structures</span></h1><span>
</span><p style="display: block; margin: 8px 0px; line-height: 1.6;"><span></span><small style="font-size: 0.8em;"><span>Published on </span><time><span>November 13, 2025</span></time><span></span></small><span></span></p><span>
</span></header><span>

</span><section style="display: block; margin: 15px 0px;"><span>
</span><h2 style="display: block; font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.75em 0px;"><span>Introduction</span></h2><span>
</span><p style="display: block; margin: 8px 0px; line-height: 1.6;"><span>This is a </span><em style="font-style: italic;"><span>comprehensive example</span></em><span> of </span><strong style="font-weight: bold;"><span>nested HTML tags</span></strong><span> working together. The </span><code style="font-family: monospace; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em;"><span>MarkedInput</span></code><span> library can parse and render </span><mark style="background-color: rgb(255, 235, 59); padding: 2px 4px;"><span>complex HTML structures</span></mark><span> with multiple levels of nesting.</span></p><span>

</span><blockquote style="display: block; border-left: 4px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); padding-left: 16px; margin: 8px 0px; font-style: italic; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span>
</span><p style="display: block; margin: 8px 0px; line-height: 1.6;"><span>HTML nesting allows us to create </span><strong style="font-weight: bold;"><span>rich, semantic documents</span></strong><span> that are both </span><em style="font-style: italic;"><span>readable</span></em><span> and </span><u style="text-decoration: underline;"><span>well-structured</span></u><span>.</span></p><span>
</span></blockquote><span>
</span></section><span>

</span><section style="display: block; margin: 15px 0px;"><span>
</span><h2 style="display: block; font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.75em 0px;"><span>Key Features</span></h2><span>
</span><ul style="display: block; list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 8px 0px;"><span>
</span><li style="display: list-item; margin: 4px 0px;"><span></span><strong style="font-weight: bold;"><span>Bold text</span></strong><span> using </span><code style="font-family: monospace; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em;"><span>&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;</span></code><span> or </span><code style="font-family: monospace; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em;"><span>&amp;lt;b&amp;gt;</span></code><span> tags</span></li><span>
</span><li style="display: list-item; margin: 4px 0px;"><span></span><em style="font-style: italic;"><span>Italic text</span></em><span> with </span><code style="font-family: monospace; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em;"><span>&amp;lt;em&amp;gt;</span></code><span> or </span><code style="font-family: monospace; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em;"><span>&amp;lt;i&amp;gt;</span></code><span> tags</span></li><span>
</span><li style="display: list-item; margin: 4px 0px;"><span></span><u style="text-decoration: underline;"><span>Underlined content</span></u><span> for emphasis</span></li><span>
</span><li style="display: list-item; margin: 4px 0px;"><span></span><mark style="background-color: rgb(255, 235, 59); padding: 2px 4px;"><span>Highlighted text</span></mark><span> to draw attention</span></li><span>
</span><li style="display: list-item; margin: 4px 0px;"><span></span><del style="text-decoration: line-through; opacity: 0.7;"><span>Strikethrough</span></del><span> for deleted content</span></li><span>
</span><li style="display: list-item; margin: 4px 0px;"><span></span><code style="font-family: monospace; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em;"><span>Inline code</span></code><span> snippets</span></li><span>
</span></ul><span>
</span></section><span>

</span><section style="display: block; margin: 15px 0px;"><span>
</span><h2 style="display: block; font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.75em 0px;"><span>Advanced Examples</span></h2><span>
</span><h3 style="display: block; font-size: 1.17em; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.83em 0px;"><span>Mathematical Notation</span></h3><span>
</span><p style="display: block; margin: 8px 0px; line-height: 1.6;"><span>The formula for water is H</span><sub style="font-size: 0.8em; vertical-align: sub;"><span>2</span></sub><span>O, and Einstein's famous equation is E=mc</span><sup style="font-size: 0.8em; vertical-align: super;"><span>2</span></sup><span>.</span></p><span>

</span><h3 style="display: block; font-size: 1.17em; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.83em 0px;"><span>Code Blocks</span></h3><span>
</span><pre style="display: block; font-family: monospace; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); padding: 12px; border-radius: 4px; overflow: auto; margin: 8px 0px;"><span></span><code style="font-family: monospace; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em;"><span>function parseHTML(input) {
  return parser.parse(input);
}</span></code><span></span></pre><span>

</span><h3 style="display: block; font-size: 1.17em; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.83em 0px;"><span>Nested Lists</span></h3><span>
</span><ol style="display: block; list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 8px 0px;"><span>
</span><li style="display: list-item; margin: 4px 0px;"><span>First level item
</span><ul style="display: block; list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 8px 0px;"><span>
</span><li style="display: list-item; margin: 4px 0px;"><span>Second level </span><strong style="font-weight: bold;"><span>nested</span></strong><span> item</span></li><span>
</span><li style="display: list-item; margin: 4px 0px;"><span>Another nested item with </span><em style="font-style: italic;"><span>emphasis</span></em><span></span></li><span>
</span></ul><span>
</span></li><span>
</span><li style="display: list-item; margin: 4px 0px;"><span>Another first level item</span></li><span>
</span></ol><span>
</span></section><span>

</span><section style="display: block; margin: 15px 0px;"><span>
</span><h2 style="display: block; font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.75em 0px;"><span>Complex Nesting</span></h2><span>
</span><div style="display: block; padding: 10px; margin: 5px 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(224, 224, 224); border-radius: 4px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);"><span>
</span><p style="display: block; margin: 8px 0px; line-height: 1.6;"><span>Here's a </span><strong style="font-weight: bold;"><span>complex example</span></strong><span> with </span><em style="font-style: italic;"><span>multiple </span><u style="text-decoration: underline;"><span>nested </span><mark style="background-color: rgb(255, 235, 59); padding: 2px 4px;"><span>tags</span></mark><span></span></u><span> inside</span></em><span> each other.</span></p><span>
</span><p style="display: block; margin: 8px 0px; line-height: 1.6;"><span>You can even have </span><code style="font-family: monospace; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em;"><span>code with </span><strong style="font-weight: bold;"><span>bold</span></strong><span> inside</span></code><span> or </span><mark style="background-color: rgb(255, 235, 59); padding: 2px 4px;"><span>highlighted </span><em style="font-style: italic;"><span>italic </span><u style="text-decoration: underline;"><span>underlined</span></u><span></span></em><span> text</span></mark><span>.</span></p><span>
</span></div><span>
</span></section><span>

</span><footer style="display: block; padding: 10px; background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240); border-top: 2px solid rgb(221, 221, 221); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.9em; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span>
</span><p style="display: block; margin: 8px 0px; line-height: 1.6;"><span></span><small style="font-size: 0.8em;"><span>© 2025 MarkedInput Library. Built with </span><strong style="font-weight: bold;"><span>React</span></strong><span> and </span><em style="font-style: italic;"><span>TypeScript</span></em><span>.</span></small><span></span></p><span>
</span></footer><span>
</span></article><span contenteditable="false"></span></div>"
`;

